  <eligibility>
    <study_pop>
      <textblock>
        About 800 teenagers are admitted each year to the pediatric departments at the Ha'Emek
        Medical Center. Three principal conditions are the causes of admission: chronic diseases,
        acute &quot;organic&quot; diseases, and psychiatric diseases including suicide attempts, anorexia,
        and others.
      </textblock>
    </study_pop>
    <sampling_method>Non-Probability Sample</sampling_method>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria: All the patients ages 14 to 20 ys admitted to the pediatric ward.

        Exclusion Criteria: No exclusion criteria relevant.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
